pages.body:
## The most important change

I have changed a behaviour of installation for controllers, modules, models, etc.. Please update external modules in your all projects to latest.

__Old version__:

```javascript
exports.install = function(framework, options) {
    // That's the past
};

exports.uninstall = function(framework, options) {
    // That's the past
};
```

__New version__:

```javascript
exports.install = function(options) {
    // framework is a global variable    
};

exports.uninstall = function(options) {
    // framework is a global variable    
};
```

__Solution for both versions__:

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
    var options = framework.version >= 1900 ? arguments[0] : arguments[1];
};

exports.uninstall = function() {
    var options = framework.version >= 1900 ? arguments[0] : arguments[1];    
};
```

__100% backward compatibility__:

You can disable this behaviour with `allow-compatibility: true` in configuration files - [documentation](http://127.0.0.1:8005/v1.9.x/en.html#api~FrameworkConfiguration~allow-compatibility).

---

## Updated json flag

I have performed a new change with `json` flag. I simplified it.

```javascript
// Old version:
F.route('/some-url/', action, ['post', 'json']);
F.route('/some-url/', action, ['put', 'json']);

// New version
F.route('/some-url/', action, ['post']);
F.route('/some-url/', action, ['put']);
```

## Replaced last argument in F.mail() and controller.mail()

I have replaced argument in `F.mail()` and `controller.mail()`. The argument `[replyTo]` has been replaced for `[language]`. So new version `v1.9.0` can localize mail content too.

- [Documentation: F.mail()](#api~Framework~framework.mail)
- [Documentation: controller.mail()](#api~FrameworkController~controller.mail)

---

## Utils.extend()

In this method has been changed a default value for `[rewrite]` from `false` to `true` [documentation](#api~FrameworkUtils~Utils.extend).

- Install [node.js platform](http://www.nodejs.org) on your computer
- [Download empty project](https://github.com/totaljs/framework/releases)
- Unpack and open in your favorite text editor:

## Create routes

Open and edit file `controllers/default.js`. This file is a controller file and it can contains actions. The action describes a response to some request. You can create unlimited count of controllers.

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
    // define routes with actions
    F.route('/', view_index);
    F.route('/services/{name}/', view_services);
    F.route('/contact/', view_contact);
    F.route('/contact/', json_contact, ['post']);
}

// The action
function view_index() {
    var self = this;
    // The "index" view is routed into the views/index.html
    // ---> Send the response
    self.view('index');
}

function view_services(name) {
    var self = this;
    // The "services" view is routed into the views/services.html
    // A second argument is the model
    // ---> Send the response
    self.view('services', { category: name });
}

function view_contact() {
    var self = this;
    // "contact" view is routed to views/contact.html
    // ---> Send the response
    self.view('contact');
}

function json_contact() {
    var self = this;

    // Get the data from the request body.
    // The data are parsed into the object automatically.
    var model = self.body;

    // e.g.
    // model.email
    // model.name

    // Send the mail to our company
    var message = self.mail('info@company.com', 'Contact form', 'mail-template', model);
    message.reply(model.email);

    // ---> and send the response in JSON format
    self.json({ success: true });
}
```

## Edit the views

### Edit view: views/layout.html

The layout view is the special view which it contains the layout. Into the view are rendered other views. You can create unlimited count of layouts.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    @{meta}
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="format-detection" content="telephone=no" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, user-scalable=no" />
    <meta name="robots" content="all,follow" />
    @{import('default.js', 'bootstrap.min.css', 'default.css', 'font-awesome.min.css', 'favicon.ico')}
</head>
<body>
    @{body}
</body>
</html>
```

- `@{meta}` renders meta tags and other stuff which you will need
- `@{import('...')}` renders tags
- `@{body}` renders view from the action (__IMPORTANT__ `@{body}` is very important for layouts)

More about the view tags in [FrameworkViews](#api~FrameworkViews).

### Edit the view: views/index.html

```html
<h1>Hello world!</h1>
<br />
<p>This is the content from the view.</p>
```

### Create the view: views/services.html

```html
@{meta('Your page title', 'Your page description', 'Your page keywords')}

<h1>@{title}</h1>
<br />

@{if model.category === 'web-applications'}
    <p>We build web application</p>
@{fi}

@{if model.category === 'mobile-applications'}
    <p>We build mobile applications</p>
@{fi}
```

### Create the view: views/contact.html

```html
@{meta('Contact us', 'Your page description', 'Your page keywords')}

<h1>@{title}</h1>
<br />
...
...
...
```

### Run the application

Open terminal / command line and __find your application directory__, then write:

```bash
$ node --harmony debug.js
```

Open `http://127.0.0.1:8000` in your web browser.

---

### Read more:

- [Total.js - Directory structure](#pages~Directory%20structure)

Controllers are responsible for responding to requests from a web browser, mobile application or any other system capable of communicating with a server. Each route is mapped into the action and the action responds to requests. The controllers with modules are the main feature of the framework logic.

```plain
Initialization: Modules --> Packages --> Models --> Definitions --> Controllers
```

The controller __knows 3x types of routes__: _classic_, _websocket_ and _file route_.

- The classic route handles a classic requests into the dynamic content (view engine).
- The websocket route handles WebSockets connections.
- The file route handles static files.

---

__More informations__

- The controller is the plain JavaScript file with `.js` extension.
- The framework automatically loads the controller into the memory.
- All controllers are stored in `your-app/controllers/` directory.
- `exports.install` is executed automatically and one time.
- Views are loaded according to the controller name `your-app/views/your-controller-name/`.
- You can create unlimited count of controllers.
- The controller can be injected from the URL address, [example](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/framework-install-controller).
- Routing supports routing according to the subdomains, [example](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/routing-subdomain).
- The controller can communicate with the other controller.

---

## Examples

Most [examples](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/) contain controllers.

- [Example: Routing](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/routing)
- [Example: Routing + Flags](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/routing-flags)
- [Example: Routing + Flags + Roles](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/routing-flags-roles)
- [Example: Routing + Generators](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/routing-generators)
- [Example: Inline routing](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/routing-inline)
- [Example: Image resizer routing](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/routing-resize)
- [Example: Subdomain routing](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/routing-subdomain)
- [Example: Routing timeout](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/routing-timeout)
- [Example: WebSocket routing](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/websocket)
- [Example: Cancel executing action in controller](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/controller-cancel)
- [Example: Sending email from action in controller](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/controller-mail)
- [Example: Cache output from action in controller](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/controller-memorize)
- [Example: Communicating between controllers between different web apps](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/controller-proxy)
- [Example: Sharing functions between controllers](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/controller-sharing)
- [Example: Transfer request to different action](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/controller-transfer)
- [Example: Install controller from URL](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/framework-install-controller)
- [Example: Project structure](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/project-structure)

---

## The definition

- Class: [FrameworkController](#api~FrameworkController)

### PROPERTY: exports.id;

`optional` Can contain only the controller name (it's the identificator name). A __default value__ for this property is the controller filename without extension.

```javascript
exports.id = 'Controller name';
```

### METHOD: exports.install;

`optional` `important` This is the initialization function of the controller.

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
    framework.route('/');
    framework.route('/api/{type}/', json_api, ['put', 'json']);
};
```

### METHOD: exports.uninstall;

`optional` This function is executed when the framework is uninstalled from the framework.

```javascript
exports.uninstall = function() {
    console.log('This controller is uninstalled.');
};
```

### METHOD: exports.usage;

`optional` This function must return exploitation of controller. [Example: Usage](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/framework-usage).

```javascript
exports.usage = function() {
    return { requests: counter };
};
```

### A full example of the controller

Filename: `controllers/default.js`

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
    framework.route('/', view_index);
    framework.route('/contact/', view_contact);
    framework.route('/hello/', plain_hello);
    framework.route('/api/codelist/', json_codelist, ['xhr', 'get']);
    framework.route('/sync/', view_sync);
};

function view_index() {
    this.view('index');
}

function view_contact() {
    this.layout('layouts/subpage');
    this.view('contact', { email: '@' });
}

function plain_hello() {
    this.plain('Hello world!');
}

function json_codelist() {
    this.mail('info@company.com', 'Codelist notifications', 'mails/codelist');
    this.json([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]);
}

// GENERATORS
function *view_sync() {
    var users = yield sync(DATABASE('users').$$all(n => n))();
    this.json(users);
}

// or an inline route
framework.route('/services/', function() {
    this.view('services');
});
```

## The routing

- Method: [framework.route()](#api~Framework~framework.route)
- Method: [framework.websocket()](#api~Framework~framework.websocket)
- Method: [framework.file()](#api~Framework~framework.file)
- List: [route flags](#api~HttpRouteOptionsFlags)

### System routing

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
    framework.route('#400', custom); // Bad Request
    framework.route('#401', custom); // Unauthorized
    framework.route('#403', custom); // Forbidden
    framework.route('#404', custom); // Not Found
    framework.route('#408', custom); // Request Timeout
    framework.route('#431', custom); // Request Header Fields Too Large
    framework.route('#500', custom); // Internal Server Error
    framework.route('#501', custom); // Not Implemented
}

function custom() {
    this.view('http-error-view');
}
```

Definitions can rewrite existing functionality or add a new. The definition can define the framework behavior and it does not have any other logic. __In short__: the definition is a coded configuration file.

```plain
Initialization: Modules --> Packages --> Models --> Definitions --> Controllers
```

__More informations__

- The definition is the plain JavaScript file with `.js` extension.
- All definitions are stored in `your-app/definitions/` directory.
- Each definitions is executed automatically and one time.
- You can create unlimited count of definitions
- The definition can be injected from the URL address, [example](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/framework-install-definition).

