## The definition

The definition file contains only the code to run, nothing more.

### A full example of definition

E.g. create: `definitions/database.js`

```javascript
var DB = null;

require('mongodb').MongoClient.connect('connection-string-to-database', function(err, db) {
    if (err)
        throw err;
    DB = db;
});

// Rewrite built-in functionality
F.database = function(collection) {
    if (collection)
        return DB.collection(collection);
    return DB;
};
```

```plain
Initialization: Modules --> Packages --> Models --> Definitions --> Controllers
```

__More informations__

- The module is the plain JavaScript file with `.js` extension.
- The framework automatically loads the module into the memory.
- All modules are stored in `your-app/modules/` directory.
- `exports.install` is executed automatically and one time.
- Views are loaded according to the controller name from `your-app/views/`.
- You can create unlimited count of modules.
- Module can be injected from the URL address, [example](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/framework-install-module).
- The module can communicate with other modules or controllers.
- [Download modules](https://github.com/totaljs/modules)

---

## Examples

- [Example: Modules](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/framework-modules)

---

## The definition

### PROPERTY: exports.id;

`optional` Can contain only the module name (it's the identificator name). A __default value__ for this property is the module filename without extension.

```javascript
exports.id = 'Module name';
```

### PROPERTY: exports.dependencies;

`optional` Can contain only the array of module names. The framework waits for all dependencies and then installs the pending modules.

```javascript
exports.dependencies = ['moduleA', 'moduleC'];
```

### METHOD: exports.install;

`optional` `important` This is the initialization function of the module. This function is executed when framework loads modules. __Modules support routing.__ Argument: `options` can contain custom settings for the module, is optional.

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
    console.log('Hello from the module.');
    F.route('/module/');
};
```

### METHOD: exports.uninstall;

`optional` This function is executed when the framework uninstalls the module. Argument: `options` can contain custom settings for the module, is optional.

```javascript
exports.uninstall = function(options) {
    console.log('This module is uninstalled.');
};
```

### METHOD: exports.usage;

`optional` This function must return exploitation of the module. [Example: Usage](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/framework-usage).

```javascript
exports.usage = function() {
    return { requests: counter };
};
```

### A full example of the module

Filename: `modules/counter.js`

```javascript
exports.id = 'counter';
exports.version = '1.01';

var counter = 0;

exports.install = function(options) {
    F.on('request', increment);
    F.route('/stats/', json_stats);
};

exports.uninstall = function(options) {
    F.removeListener('request', increment);
};

exports.usage = function() {
    return { requests: counter };
}

function json_stats() {
    // The same behavior like in the controller
    this.json({ requests: counter });
}

function increment() {
    counter++;
}
```

